The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Saturday, June 04, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Burdwan, June 3: Half-a-dozen people have died because of heat in Burdwan and Bankura since last night. 

 Health officials said among the dead was a seven-year-old girl. Burdwan town today recorded a maximum temperature of 44.5 degrees Celsius and Bankura 45.2. The heat wave has claimed 11 lives in the districts in two days. Today, Nanigopal Hazra, 43, a fruit seller, died of dehydration and Sunil Majhi, 62, who was returning home at Asansol after visiting his daughter at Barabani, 220 km from Calcutta, suffered a heat stroke. Paturi Majhi of Andal and a milkman also did not survive the heat. In Bankura, Basudeb Mondal, 56, died last night. 

 Calcutta: The Bengal Petroleum Dealers Association has called a strike on June 20 opposing the likely hike in prices.




